Space researchers have only known about the existence of dark matter for about ten years.
It is evident from it that an attraction occurs, whose effect on other celestial bodies can be observed.
On the other hand, it itself is completely invisible, i.e. it sends and reflects no electromagnetic radiation, especially no visible light.
According to the calculations of the scientists, the dark matter makes up at least one fifth of the entire mass of the universe.
