In view of these scientific findings, we need to re-examine the existing control systems so that they are fully effective and keep pace with the new technology".
Brussels had commissioned the independent scientific committee in view of the widespread use of portable music equipment among young people.
"The scientists - the EU's Communication concludes - confirm that there is too much concern and that the European Commission, together with the other Members of the European Union and those concerned, will now examine the necessary measures to better protect children and young people from the noise that comes from portable music devices and similar devices."
